title: The NFL world was in awe of Jared Cook’s catch
text:
The NFL world was in awe of Jared Cook’s catch What a throw. What a catch. Post to Facebook The NFL world was in awe of Jared Cook’s catch What a throw. What a catch.  //usat.ly/2iB03Tj   Join the Nation's Conversation   The NFL world was in awe of Jared Cook’s catch Andrew Joseph 8:30   
The Green Bay Packers are heading to the NFC title game in Atlanta thanks to more late-game magic from Aaron Rodgers, but nobody is going to overlook the incredible effort from Jared Cook. 
With the Packers facing a third-and-20 in their own territory, Rodgers scrambled to his left and let an unbalanced throw loose near the sideline. Cook came out of nowhere to make the catch and keep his feet inbounds. Both the throw and catch were stunning. The catch set up Mason Crosby's game-winning field goal. 
The football world couldn't believe Cook pulled that catch off. Read or Share this story: http://usat.ly/2iB03Tj Most Popular
